<script lang="ts">import{onMount}from'svelte';import{getCategories,getMetrics,type Category,type Metric}from'$lib/api';let categories=$state<Category[]>([]),metrics=$state<Metric[]>([]);onMount(async()=>[categories,metrics]=await Promise.all([getCategories(),getMetrics()]));</script>
<svelte:head><title>Methodology · StateScore</title></svelte:head><div class="page-head"><div><p class="eyebrow">Read the fine print</p><h1>Methodology</h1><p>StateScore is a comparison lens, not a verdict. This page documents every choice between a public statistic and the number you see.</p></div></div><div class="formula"><span>metric values</span><b>→</b><span>0–100 scores</span><b>→</b><span>category scores</span><b>→</b><span>overall score</span></div><section class="prose card"><h2>How a score is built</h2><div class="columns"><div><h3>Normalize each metric</h3><p>Metrics with different units become comparable scores from 0 to 100. Percentile rank is the default: a state’s position among peers determines its score. These are relative ranks, not absolute grades — if every state worsens, the top score can still look high.</p></div><div><h3>As-of year</h3><p>Each ranking uses one as-of year. For every metric, StateScore takes the latest value at or before that year so staggered releases (for example 2022 longevity with 2024 safety data) still form one coherent composite.</p></div><div><h3>Respect direction</h3><p>For income and attainment, higher values score better. For unemployment, crime, and costs, lower values score better. Direction is listed for every active metric below.</p></div><div><h3>Canonical backend scores</h3><p>The Go backend normalizes and stores score snapshots. The UI reads those snapshots. Weight changes on Your priorities only re-average the already-normalized category scores.</p></div><div><h3>Active metrics only</h3><p>Metrics without imported coverage are inactive and omitted from rankings so empty pillars do not silently steal weight via redistribution.</p></div><div><h3>Keep missing data visible</h3><p>A missing value never becomes zero. The metric is excluded and its weight is redistributed within its category. Incomplete scores carry a completeness warning.</p></div></div></section><section><p class="eyebrow">Active lenses</p><div class="category-list">{#each categories.filter(c=>metrics.some(m=>m.categoryId===c.id)) as c}<article><b>{c.name}</b><p>{c.description}</p><span>{metrics.filter(m=>m.categoryId===c.id).length} active measures · {Math.round(c.defaultWeight*100)}% category default</span></article>{/each}</div></section><section class="card metric-list"><h2>Active metric definitions</h2>{#each categories.filter(c=>metrics.some(m=>m.categoryId===c.id)) as c}<details open><summary><strong>{c.name}</strong><span>{metrics.filter(m=>m.categoryId===c.id).length} measures</span></summary>{#each metrics.filter(m=>m.categoryId===c.id) as m}<div class="metric"><div><b>{m.name}</b><p>{m.description}</p></div><dl><div><dt>Unit</dt><dd>{m.unit}</dd></div><div><dt>Direction</dt><dd>{m.higherIsBetter?'Higher is better':'Lower is better'}</dd></div><div><dt>Normalization</dt><dd>{m.normalizationMethod}</dd></div><div><dt>Weight</dt><dd>{Math.round(m.defaultWeight*100)}%</dd></div></dl></div>{/each}</details>{/each}</section><section class="limits"><h2>Limitations</h2><p>Scores are ordinal comparisons among states on the included metrics for an as-of year — not absolute quality. Public datasets release on different schedules, and statewide averages conceal local variation. A high score does not describe every community. Rankings are sensitive to which metrics are active, available years, and the weights you choose. Use StateScore to ask sharper questions—not to end the conversation.</p></section>
<style>.formula{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;align-items:center;justify-content:center;gap:1rem;margin-bottom:2rem;padding:1rem;border-block:1px solid var(--line);font:700 .8rem var(--font-data);text-transform:uppercase}.formula b{color:var(--coral)}.prose h2,.metric-list h2,.limits h2{font:400 2rem var(--font-display);margin-top:0}.columns{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr);gap:1.5rem}.columns h3{margin-bottom:.3rem;color:var(--blue)}.columns p{margin-top:0;color:var(--muted)}.category-list{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(140px,1fr));gap:.6rem;margin-bottom:2rem}.category-list article{border-top:5px solid var(--lake);padding:1rem 0}.category-list article:nth-child(2){border-color:#4c75a3}.category-list article:nth-child(3){border-color:#55a67a}.category-list article:nth-child(4){border-color:#d89045}.category-list article:nth-child(5){border-color:var(--coral)}.category-list p,.category-list span{font-size:.8rem;color:var(--muted)}details{border-top:1px solid var(--line)}summary{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;padding:1rem 0;cursor:pointer}.metric{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1.4fr;gap:2rem;padding:1rem;background:var(--paper);margin-bottom:.5rem}.metric p{margin:.2rem 0;color:var(--muted)}dl{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);margin:0}dt{font-size:.65rem;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted)}dd{margin:0;font-size:.85rem}.limits{max-width:800px;margin:4rem auto 0;text-align:center}.limits p{color:var(--muted)}@media(max-width:850px){.category-list{grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr)}.metric{grid-template-columns:1fr}.metric dl{grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr);gap:.8rem}}@media(max-width:600px){.columns,.category-list{grid-template-columns:1fr}}</style>
